, and to restructure the mechanisms responsible for the state of the earth. "--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on print version record.  a44 0aNature in motion pictures. 0aEcology in motion pictures. 0aEnvironmental protection and motion pictures.1 aNarine, Anil,eeditor of compilation. 0aRoutledge advances in film studies ;v33.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&scope=site&db=nlebk&db=nlabk&AN=849964z(Single User Access)  wORDERhUAINzPDACOUTTS  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6756197-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu12/9/2014xE-BOOKzPDAOWNED01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2014030006bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/308754422